name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: And just as many organisations didn't have to pay ransomware to be saved from WannaCry, there may not be a mandatory vaccine for COVID-19 afterall. In any case, we want our normal lives back!

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: As Marcus Hutchins saved the internet by finding the 'kill switch' of WannaCry, gaining fame and fortune as a result, the world also needs to be saved from COVID-19 and it's attendant socio-economic challenges.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: The world eventually saw the end of WannaCry but that didn't stop the writing of other computer viruses and the existing ones from infecting vulnerable computers, as it were.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: There were cybercriminals behind WannaCry. The Justice Department had indicted a hacker linked to the state-sponsored hacking team in North Korea, as being responsible for WannaCry.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: Hutchins was able to detach WannaCry from it's control address by registering another domain and redirecting the worms to receive new commands from the new domain.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: WannaCry, Hutchins discovered, had a command-and-control address. It spreads to systems without harm until it receives a command from the address to infect and attack. But once detached from it's command-and-control address, it was harmless even though it continued to spread.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: To analyse and stop its ravaging attacks, infected systems were isolated from the network. A cybersecurity researcher and one time kingpin of the notorious dark-web, Marcus Hutchins, had to quarantine snippets of WannaCry's codes in a virtual machine to monitor its behaviour.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: To free and unlock your infected computers, authors of WannaCry, demanded for a ransom of $300 per infected computer to be paid in bitcoins - for obvious reasons.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: WannaCry, in the same vein, spread globally by adopting a Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) approach, crippling economic activities in it's wake and causing companies and institutions whose networks it shutdown to lose, on aggregate, over $8 billion USD within days.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: Interestingly, WannaCry also, allegedly originated from the Far East - North Korea, a country China shares borders with.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet:
WannaCry vs COVID-19

WannaCry was a malware, if you like, a digital plague that devoured the world's networks in 2017, infecting tens of thousands of computers. Like COVID-19, the global scale of WannaCry's attack was enormous - a ransomware pandemic.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: And just as many organisations didn't have to pay ransomware to be saved from WannaCry, there may not be a mandatory vaccine for COVID-19 afterall. In any case, we want our normal lives back!

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: As Marcus Hutchins saved the internet by finding the 'kill switch' of WannaCry, gaining fame and fortune as a result, the world also needs to be saved from COVID-19 and it's attendant socio-economic challenges.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: The world eventually saw the end of WannaCry but that didn't stop the writing of other computer viruses and the existing ones from infecting vulnerable computers, as it were.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: There were cybercriminals behind WannaCry. The Justice Department had indicted a hacker linked to the state-sponsored hacking team in North Korea, as being responsible for WannaCry.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: Hutchins was able to detach WannaCry from it's control address by registering another domain and redirecting the worms to receive new commands from the new domain.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: WannaCry, Hutchins discovered, had a command-and-control address. It spreads to systems without harm until it receives a command from the address to infect and attack. But once detached from it's command-and-control address, it was harmless even though it continued to spread.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: To analyse and stop its ravaging attacks, infected systems were isolated from the network. A cybersecurity researcher and one time kingpin of the notorious dark-web, Marcus Hutchins, had to quarantine snippets of WannaCry's codes in a virtual machine to monitor its behaviour.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: To free and unlock your infected computers, authors of WannaCry, demanded for a ransom of $300 per infected computer to be paid in bitcoins - for obvious reasons.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: WannaCry, in the same vein, spread globally by adopting a Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) approach, crippling economic activities in it's wake and causing companies and institutions whose networks it shutdown to lose, on aggregate, over $8 billion USD within days.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: Interestingly, WannaCry also, allegedly originated from the Far East - North Korea, a country China shares borders with.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet:
WannaCry vs COVID-19

WannaCry was a malware, if you like, a digital plague that devoured the world's networks in 2017, infecting tens of thousands of computers. Like COVID-19, the global scale of WannaCry's attack was enormous - a ransomware pandemic.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: And just as many organisations didn't have to pay ransomware to be saved from WannaCry, there may not be a mandatory vaccine for COVID-19 afterall. In any case, we want our normal lives back!

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: As Marcus Hutchins saved the internet by finding the 'kill switch' of WannaCry, gaining fame and fortune as a result, the world also needs to be saved from COVID-19 and it's attendant socio-economic challenges.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: The world eventually saw the end of WannaCry but that didn't stop the writing of other computer viruses and the existing ones from infecting vulnerable computers, as it were.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: There were cybercriminals behind WannaCry. The Justice Department had indicted a hacker linked to the state-sponsored hacking team in North Korea, as being responsible for WannaCry.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: Hutchins was able to detach WannaCry from it's control address by registering another domain and redirecting the worms to receive new commands from the new domain.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: WannaCry, Hutchins discovered, had a command-and-control address. It spreads to systems without harm until it receives a command from the address to infect and attack. But once detached from it's command-and-control address, it was harmless even though it continued to spread.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: To analyse and stop its ravaging attacks, infected systems were isolated from the network. A cybersecurity researcher and one time kingpin of the notorious dark-web, Marcus Hutchins, had to quarantine snippets of WannaCry's codes in a virtual machine to monitor its behaviour.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: To free and unlock your infected computers, authors of WannaCry, demanded for a ransom of $300 per infected computer to be paid in bitcoins - for obvious reasons.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: WannaCry, in the same vein, spread globally by adopting a Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) approach, crippling economic activities in it's wake and causing companies and institutions whose networks it shutdown to lose, on aggregate, over $8 billion USD within days.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet: Interestingly, WannaCry also, allegedly originated from the Far East - North Korea, a country China shares borders with.

name: Henry Eletuo
tweet:
WannaCry vs COVID-19

WannaCry was a malware, if you like, a digital plague that devoured the world's networks in 2017, infecting tens of thousands of computers. Like COVID-19, the global scale of WannaCry's attack was enormous - a ransomware pandemic.
